com.rockhoppertech.music.chord

Class ChordFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.rockhoppertech.music.chord.ChordFactory

  • public class ChordFactory
extends Object
    GoF Factory design pattern for chords.

    The definitions are stored in an XML file named "choarddefs.xml".

    Author:
    Gene De Lisa

      • degreesToIntervals

        public static int[] degreesToIntervals(String spelling)
        The intervals are in relation to the root. So "1 3 5" returns "4 7" and not "4 3". 
         int[] intervals = ChordFactory.degreesToIntervals("1 3 5");
        Parameters:
        spelling - A chord spelling as a String
        Returns:
        The intervals as an int[]
        See Also:
        Interval

        Returns:
        a Chord based on the registered symbol.

      • createFromDescription

        public static Chord createFromDescription(String description)
        Loop through registered chords to find a description match. 

         Chord chord = ChordFactory.createFromDescription(ChordFactory.MAJOR);
        returns a chord with its root set to Pitch.C5 (middle c), the symbol to "maj" inversion = 0, intervals = 4,7
        Parameters:
        description - A registered chord description
        Returns:
        a Chord
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the description is not in the Factory's registry
        See Also:
        createFromSymbol(String)

      • createFromIntervals

        public static Chord createFromIntervals(int[] someIntervals)
                                 throws UnknownChordException
        Loop through registered chords to find a match on intervals. 
         Chord chord = ChordFactory.createFromIntervals(new int[] { 4, 7 });
        Parameters:
        someIntervals - the intervals
        Returns:
        a Chord
        Throws:
        UnknownChordException - if the chord is unknown
        IllegalArgumentException - if the intervals are not in the Factory's registry
